summary: earlier phil thought it would be funny to run up behind me and jump on my back and force me to give him a piggy back which only...
body:
earlier phil thought it would be funny to run up behind me and jump on my back and force me to give him a piggy back

which only lasted three seconds at most before we both fell to the ground and hurt ourselves

definitely something that should’ve been cute relationship goals, but in reality no not at all

- dan

title: the water might be lovely

chapter 7

rating: M (spiciness imminent)

Summary: A month before his exam re-sit, a lonely and sad Dan runs away to the Isle of Man. Seeking escape, Dan gets more than he bargained for when he rents out a room from happy-go-lucky, recent grad, Phil Lester.

excerpt:

Dan suppresses a smile – fondness spreading through his body like warm honey.

“Wow, you take such good care of me, Phil.” He jokes, (only half-kidding by this point).

Smiling a toothy grin, Phil pokes Dan’s dimple. “Someone has to.”
